Modern italian cello made in 2023 in Madrid, Spain. It is built according to the construction techniques of the old Cremona school of 1700. The woods used for this cello are:

For the soundboard, red male spruce from Italy's Fiemme Valley was used, while flamed maple from the Balkans with constant flame was used for the back, neck and sides.

It is a newly built instrument of golden reddish brown color with yellow reflections.

The cello is in perfect condition.

Certification: n/a
